HEADWORD: Wardmote
<hw>Ward"mote`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Anciently, a
meeting of the inhabitants of a ward; also, a court formerly held in
each ward of London for trying defaults in matters relating to the
watch, police, and the like.</def> <au>Brande & C.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧Wards and
<xex>wardmotes</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Piers Plowman.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

